# Modern Material Supply - Building Materials Website

A clean, professional static website for a building materials supply business in Mauritania, built with React and Tailwind CSS.

## Features

- ✅ 5 Complete Pages (Home, Products, Services, About, Contact)
- ✅ Fully Mobile Responsive
- ✅ Clean, Professional Design
- ✅ Fast Loading with Vite
- ✅ Easy to Customize
- ✅ WhatsApp Integration
- ✅ Smooth Scrolling Navigation

## Quick Start

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 2. Run Development Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

The site will be available at `http://localhost:5173`

### 3. Build for Production

```bash
npm run build
```

This creates an optimized production build in the `dist` folder.

### 4. Preview Production Build

```bash
npm run preview
```

## Customization Guide

### Change Company Name

In `src/App.jsx`, search for "BuildMart" and replace with your company name:

```jsx
<h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600">YourCompanyName</h1>
```

### Update Contact Information

In the `Contact` component in `src/App.jsx`, update:

- **Phone**: Replace `+222 1234 5678`
- **WhatsApp**: Replace `+22212345678` in the `wa.me` URLs
- **Email**: Replace `info@buildmart.mr`
- **Location**: Update the address text

```jsx
<a href="tel:+22212345678">+222 1234 5678</a>
<a href="https://wa.me/22212345678">+222 1234 5678</a>
<a href="mailto:info@buildmart.mr">info@buildmart.mr</a>
```

### Modify Products

In the `Products` component, edit the `productCategories` array:

```jsx
const productCategories = [
  {
    name: "Your Category Name",
    description: "Category description",
    items: ["Item 1", "Item 2", "Item 3"],
  },
  // Add more categories...
];
```

### Update Services

In the `Services` component, edit the `services` array to match your offerings.

### Change Colors

The site uses blue as the primary color. To change it:

1. Open `src/App.jsx`
2. Search for `blue-` (e.g., `bg-blue-600`, `text-blue-600`)
3. Replace with your preferred color:
   - `red-600`, `green-600`, `purple-600`, etc.
   - Or use custom Tailwind colors

### Modify Content

All content is in `src/App.jsx`. Each section is a separate component:

- `Hero` - Home page intro and mission
- `Products` - Product categories
- `Services` - Additional services page
- `About` - About us section
- `Contact` - Contact information
- `Footer` - Footer content

### Add Images

To add images:

1. Create a `public/images` folder
2. Add your images there
3. Reference them in the code:

```jsx
<img src="/images/your-image.jpg" alt="Description" />
```

Example in the Hero section:

```jsx
<div className="mt-8">
  <img
    src="/images/hero-banner.jpg"
    alt="Building materials"
    className="rounded-lg shadow-xl"
  />
</div>
```

### Business Hours

Update in the `Contact` component:

```jsx
<div className="flex justify-between">
  <span className="text-gray-700">Your Days</span>
  <span className="font-semibold text-gray-900">Your Hours</span>
</div>
```

## Project Structure

```
buildmart-mauritania/
├── index.html              # Entry HTML file
├── package.json            # Dependencies and scripts
├── vite.config.js          # Vite configuration
├── tailwind.config.js      # Tailwind CSS configuration
├── postcss.config.js       # PostCSS configuration
└── src/
    ├── main.jsx            # React entry point
    ├── App.jsx             # Main application with all components
    └── index.css           # Global styles and Tailwind imports
```

## Deployment

### Option 1: Netlify (Recommended)

1. Push your code to GitHub
2. Connect to Netlify
3. Build command: `npm run build`
4. Publish directory: `dist`

### Option 2: Vercel

1. Push your code to GitHub
2. Import to Vercel
3. It auto-detects Vite configuration

### Option 3: Traditional Hosting

1. Run `npm run build`
2. Upload the `dist` folder to your web host
3. Point your domain to the uploaded files

## Tech Stack

- **React 18** - UI library
- **Vite** - Build tool and dev server
- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **Lucide React** - Icon library

## Performance

- Optimized for fast loading
- Minimal dependencies
- Responsive images ready
- Production build is highly compressed

## Browser Support

- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Edge (latest)
- Mobile browsers

## Customization Tips

1. **Keep it simple** - The design is intentionally clean and professional
2. **Mobile first** - Test on mobile devices regularly
3. **Optimize images** - Compress images before adding them
4. **SEO** - Update the meta description in `index.html`
5. **Analytics** - Add Google Analytics in `index.html` if needed

